title: Saturday’s Prep Volleyball results
text:
Published: Mon, October 12, 2015 @ 12:00 a.m. 
East Palestine 25-25-21-25, Jackson-Milton 22-16-25-22 
NORTH JACKSON 
Marlaina Frye and Jenn Rhodes each scored 12 points, Jessica Leake had 16 kills and Brysten Trosky had 13 kills as the Bulldogs (5-14) beat the Bluejays (8-11). Leake also had seven digs and three blocks and Frye had 17 assists. Amy Ritchie had 12 points, eight kills and five blocks and Julissa Tomaino had eight kills for Jackson-Milton. 
Heartland Christian 25-25-25, 
Valley Christian 17-13-7 
COLUMBIANA 
Bonnie Flynn had 12 points, 30 kills and 16 digs and Brianna LaRocca had 27 assists and 12 digs as the Lions (11-9) beat the Eagles. Jacqueline Chapman added 15 points and five kills for Heartland Christian. India Snyder had 20 assists, Arlivian Cheirs had nine kills and Marissa Davis had 56 digs for Valley Christian. 
Staff report
